# Computer Station

### *Instructors:* Anirudh Pal and Nathan Cohen

### *Age Group:* Older Kids

### *Lesson Number:* 4 (Day 5)

### *Lesson Focus:* Introduction to C and Python

### *Lesson Objective:* An introduction to the programming languages C and Python.

### *Safety/Management Considerations:*

* The computer lab is a safe environment; anything that might be dangerous will be put away. 
* We will only have 8 stations that will be operational.
* We will heavily rely on team leaders and floaters to assist with proceedings of the lab sessions.

### *Equipment:*

* 8 Computer Stations
* RaspberryPi Server
* Projector

## Description

### *Introduction:*

* State Lesson Objective.
* Establish Directives.

### *Activity 1 - Read and Execute:*

In this activity campers will use previous experience to follow instructions presented to the in a website.

### *Activity 2 - Hello World C:*

Write a hello world program in C.

### *Activity 3 - Hello World Python:*

Write a hello world program in Python.

### *Conclusion:*

* Conclude Lesson Objectives
